null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1245251777","cve_id":"CVE-2026-38766","name":"CVE-2026-38766","owner":"D7EAD","full_name":"D7EAD/CVE-2026-38766","html_url":"https://github.com/D7EAD/CVE-2026-38766","description":"An issue in Unistal Systems Pvt. Ltd. Protegent 360 v2.0.0.4 allows a local attacker to escalate privileges via a kernel mode driver.","stargazers_count":"1","vuln_description":null,"created_at":"2026-05-21 12:49:32","updated_at":"2026-05-21 12:49:41","pushed_at":"2026-05-21 12:49:33","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 16:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1245251260","cve_id":"CVE-2026-38765","name":"CVE-2026-38765","owner":"D7EAD","full_name":"D7EAD/CVE-2026-38765","html_url":"https://github.com/D7EAD/CVE-2026-38765","description":"An issue in Unistal Systems Pvt. Ltd. Protegent 360 v2.0.0.4 allows a local attacker to escalate privileges via the kernel driver pgsecdl.sys","stargazers_count":"1","vuln_description":null,"created_at":"2026-05-21 12:48:35","updated_at":"2026-05-21 12:48:43","pushed_at":"2026-05-21 12:48:36","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 16:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1245250893","cve_id":"CVE-2026-38764","name":"CVE-2026-38764","owner":"D7EAD","full_name":"D7EAD/CVE-2026-38764","html_url":"https://github.com/D7EAD/CVE-2026-38764","description":"An issue in Unistal Systems Pvt. Ltd. Protegent 360 v2.0.0.4 allows a local attacker to escalate privileges via the kernel driver pgsecdl.sys","stargazers_count":"1","vuln_description":null,"created_at":"2026-05-21 12:47:54","updated_at":"2026-05-21 12:48:08","pushed_at":"2026-05-21 12:47:55","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 16:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1245250368","cve_id":"CVE-2026-38763","name":"CVE-2026-38763","owner":"D7EAD","full_name":"D7EAD/CVE-2026-38763","html_url":"https://github.com/D7EAD/CVE-2026-38763","description":"An issue in Unistal Systems Pvt. Ltd. Protegent 360 v2.0.0.4 allows a local attacker to cause a denial of service in the kernel.","stargazers_count":"1","vuln_description":null,"created_at":"2026-05-21 12:47:01","updated_at":"2026-05-21 12:47:27","pushed_at":"2026-05-21 12:47:02","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 16:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1245195069","cve_id":"CVE-2013-1814","name":"java-vulnerable","owner":"dannyEndorTest","full_name":"dannyEndorTest/java-vulnerable","html_url":"https://github.com/dannyEndorTest/java-vulnerable","description":"EXPOSURE demo target: Tomcat (CVE-2016-0714) + Apache Rave (CVE-2013-1814) + Java filter-padding deps","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":null,"created_at":"2026-05-21 11:11:48","updated_at":"2026-05-21 11:39:02","pushed_at":"2026-05-21 12:12:59","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 16:36:29","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1245168511","cve_id":"CVE-2025-22442","name":"android-workprofile-exploit","owner":"Hasan-Al-Hussein","full_name":"Hasan-Al-Hussein/android-workprofile-exploit","html_url":"https://github.com/Hasan-Al-Hussein/android-workprofile-exploit","description":"Research project demonstrating CVE-2025-22442 Android work-profile exploitation and data exfiltration","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":null,"created_at":"2026-05-21 10:23:55","updated_at":"2026-05-21 11:20:47","pushed_at":"2026-05-21 10:39:12","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 16:36:33","cvss_score":7,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1245135553","cve_id":"CVE-2018-21268","name":"node-vulnerable","owner":"dannyEndorTest","full_name":"dannyEndorTest/node-vulnerable","html_url":"https://github.com/dannyEndorTest/node-vulnerable","description":"Synthetic demo target for EXPOSURE — CVE-2018-21268 (traceroute) + CVE-2018-3757 (pdf-image)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":null,"created_at":"2026-05-21 09:20:15","updated_at":"2026-05-21 09:20:38","pushed_at":"2026-05-21 12:00:12","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 16:36:30","cvss_score":10,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1245106276","cve_id":"CVE-2026-45321","name":"mini-shai-hulud-detector","owner":"prashanthnataraj","full_name":"prashanthnataraj/mini-shai-hulud-detector","html_url":"https://github.com/prashanthnataraj/mini-shai-hulud-detector","description":"One-command scanner for the Mini Shai-Hulud npm supply-chain worm (CVE-2026-45321). Detect before rotating tokens.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"On 2026-05-11, between approximately 19:20 and 19:26 UTC, 84 malicious versions across 42 @tanstack/* packages were published to the npm registry. The publishes were authenticated via the legitimate GitHub Actions OIDC trusted-publisher binding for TanStack/router, but the publish workflow itself was not modified. The attacker chained three known vulnerability classes — a pull_request_target \"Pwn Request\" misconfiguration, GitHub Actions cache poisoning across the fork↔base trust boundary, and runtime memory extraction of the OIDC token from the Actions runner process — to publish credential-stealing malware under a trusted identity. Each affected package received exactly two malicious versions, published a few minutes apart.","created_at":"2026-05-21 08:16:16","updated_at":"2026-05-21 09:12:26","pushed_at":"2026-05-21 09:12:22","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 10:36:35","cvss_score":9.6,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1245095402","cve_id":"CVE-2020-25078","name":"abyss-c2","owner":"flags-alt","full_name":"flags-alt/abyss-c2","html_url":"https://github.com/flags-alt/abyss-c2","description":" ABYSS C2 — HiSilicon DVR Exploit Framework (CVE-2020-25078). Educational IoT security research platform.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"An issue was discovered on D-Link DCS-2530L before 1.06.01 Hotfix and DCS-2670L through 2.02 devices. The unauthenticated /config/getuser endpoint allows for remote administrator password disclosure.","created_at":"2026-05-21 07:54:01","updated_at":"2026-05-21 07:55:03","pushed_at":"2026-05-21 07:54:59","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 10:36:31","cvss_score":7.5,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1245051627","cve_id":"CVE-2026-2587","name":"CVE-2026-2587-Exploit-POC","owner":"Bhanunamikaze","full_name":"Bhanunamikaze/CVE-2026-2587-Exploit-POC","html_url":"https://github.com/Bhanunamikaze/CVE-2026-2587-Exploit-POC","description":"PoC validator for CVE-2026-2587 — Critical (CVSS 9.6) EL Injection RCE in Eclipse GlassFish < 7.1.0 admin console gadget handler. Multi-target scanner with CSV/JSON output.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A critical Remote Code Execution (RCE) vulnerability was identified in the server-side template rendering mechanism used by the Glassfish gadget handler. The application processes .xml files and evaluates user-supplied values within a context where Expression Language (EL) “expressions” are processed without proper sanitization or escaping. By injecting expressions such as #{7*7}, the server returns 49, confirming server-side EL evaluation. This issue allows a remote attacker to fully compromise the underlying host, enabling capabilities as reading/modifying data, executing arbitrary commands, persistence, and lateral movement.","created_at":"2026-05-21 06:31:14","updated_at":"2026-05-21 07:31:48","pushed_at":"2026-05-21 07:31:43","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 10:36:35","cvss_score":9.6,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1245031652","cve_id":"CVE-2018-14847","name":"VULNERAVEL-CVE-2018-14847---CREDENCIAIS-EXTRAIDAS","owner":"mourafuseti","full_name":"mourafuseti/VULNERAVEL-CVE-2018-14847---CREDENCIAIS-EXTRAIDAS","html_url":"https://github.com/mourafuseti/VULNERAVEL-CVE-2018-14847---CREDENCIAIS-EXTRAIDAS","description":"VULNERAVEL CVE-2018-14847 - CREDENCIAIS EXTRAIDAS MIKROTIK EM PYTHON","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"MikroTik RouterOS through 6.42 allows unauthenticated remote attackers to read arbitrary files and remote authenticated attackers to write arbitrary files due to a directory traversal vulnerability in the WinBox interface.","created_at":"2026-05-21 05:58:01","updated_at":"2026-05-21 06:19:54","pushed_at":"2026-05-21 06:19:48","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 10:36:31","cvss_score":9.1,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1244946141","cve_id":"CVE-2026-30950","name":"autogpt-CVE-2026-30950-poc","owner":"ZeroPathAI","full_name":"ZeroPathAI/autogpt-CVE-2026-30950-poc","html_url":"https://github.com/ZeroPathAI/autogpt-CVE-2026-30950-poc","description":"POC for CVE-2026-30950 which allows session hijacking in AutoGpt","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"AutoGPT is a workflow automation platform for creating, deploying, and managing continuous artificial intelligence agents. Versions 0.6.36 through 0.6.50 are vulnerable to Authenticated Session Hijacking via IDOR. If an authenticated attacker can determine the session_id of another user's session, they can take it over, reading any messages in it and locking the legitimate user out. The PATCH /sessions/{session_id}/assign-user endpoint authenticates the caller but never verifies session ownership: the service layer invokes the session lookup with user_id=None, which the data access layer interprets as a privileged/system call that bypasses the ownership filter, allowing any authenticated user to reassign an arbitrary session to themselves. This issue has been patched in version 0.6.51.","created_at":"2026-05-21 03:55:58","updated_at":"2026-05-21 07:38:57","pushed_at":"2026-05-21 07:38:54","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 10:36:35","cvss_score":7.1,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244824112","cve_id":"CVE-2024-4367","name":"CVE-2024-4367-PDF.js-xss","owner":"xiaoqiesec0x1","full_name":"xiaoqiesec0x1/CVE-2024-4367-PDF.js-xss","html_url":"https://github.com/xiaoqiesec0x1/CVE-2024-4367-PDF.js-xss","description":"CVE-2024-4367–PDF.js-xss","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A type check was missing when handling fonts in PDF.js, which would allow arbitrary JavaScript execution in the PDF.js context. This vulnerability affects Firefox < 126, Firefox ESR < 115.11, and Thunderbird < 115.11.","created_at":"2026-05-21 01:24:54","updated_at":"2026-05-21 01:28:06","pushed_at":"2026-05-21 01:25:00","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 04:36:33","cvss_score":5.6,"severity":"MEDIUM"},{"id":"1244777367","cve_id":"CVE-2021-41773","name":"CVE-2021-41773-PoC","owner":"wvverez","full_name":"wvverez/CVE-2021-41773-PoC","html_url":"https://github.com/wvverez/CVE-2021-41773-PoC","description":"「🪶」PoC (Proof of concept) of Path traversal + RCE in Apache HTTP Server 2.4.49","stargazers_count":"1","vuln_description":"A flaw was found in a change made to path normalization in Apache HTTP Server 2.4.49. An attacker could use a path traversal attack to map URLs to files outside the directories configured by Alias-like directives. If files outside of these directories are not protected by the usual default configuration \"require all denied\", these requests can succeed. If CGI scripts are also enabled for these aliased pathes, this could allow for remote code execution. This issue is known to be exploited in the wild. This issue only affects Apache 2.4.49 and not earlier versions. The fix in Apache HTTP Server 2.4.50 was found to be incomplete, see CVE-2021-42013.","created_at":"2026-05-21 00:31:12","updated_at":"2026-05-21 02:42:33","pushed_at":"2026-05-21 02:42:28","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 04:36:31","cvss_score":7.5,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244687013","cve_id":"CVE-2024-37054","name":"CVE-2024-37054","owner":"vanhari","full_name":"vanhari/CVE-2024-37054","html_url":"https://github.com/vanhari/CVE-2024-37054","description":"a proof-of-concept for MLflow RCE (remote code execution)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Deserialization of untrusted data can occur in versions of the MLflow platform running version 0.9.0 or newer, enabling a maliciously uploaded PyFunc model to run arbitrary code on an end user’s system when interacted with.","created_at":"2026-05-20 22:54:35","updated_at":"2026-05-20 22:56:19","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 22:54:36","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 04:36:33","cvss_score":8.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244634269","cve_id":"CVE-2023-32233","name":"gemini-2.5-pro-nf-tables-red-teaming","owner":"Destawell","full_name":"Destawell/gemini-2.5-pro-nf-tables-red-teaming","html_url":"https://github.com/Destawell/gemini-2.5-pro-nf-tables-red-teaming","description":"Gemini 2.5 Pro nf_tables Red Teaming Case Study (CVE-2023-32233) — LLM Safety Alignment & Responsible Disclosure","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"In the Linux kernel through 6.3.1, a use-after-free in Netfilter nf_tables when processing batch requests can be abused to perform arbitrary read and write operations on kernel memory. Unprivileged local users can obtain root privileges. This occurs because anonymous sets are mishandled.","created_at":"2026-05-20 21:58:23","updated_at":"2026-05-20 22:05:24","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 22:05:15","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 04:36:32","cvss_score":7.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244630597","cve_id":"CVE-2025-8110","name":"CVE-2025-8110-PoC","owner":"mananispiwpiw","full_name":"mananispiwpiw/CVE-2025-8110-PoC","html_url":"https://github.com/mananispiwpiw/CVE-2025-8110-PoC","description":"CVE-2025-8110 Proof of Concept","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Improper Symbolic link handling in the PutContents API in Gogs allows Local Execution of Code.","created_at":"2026-05-20 21:54:20","updated_at":"2026-05-20 22:36:58","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 22:35:41","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 04:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1244586606","cve_id":"CVE-2025-8110","name":"coreweave-demo-2026-05","owner":"get-xor","full_name":"get-xor/coreweave-demo-2026-05","html_url":"https://github.com/get-xor/coreweave-demo-2026-05","description":"Verified vulnerability journey for CVE-2025-8110 (Gogs) and CVE-2025-3248 (Langflow) — risk triage, exploitability verification, verified patches.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Improper Symbolic link handling in the PutContents API in Gogs allows Local Execution of Code.","created_at":"2026-05-20 21:04:51","updated_at":"2026-05-20 21:06:51","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 21:06:21","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 22:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1244551945","cve_id":"CVE-2026-46300","name":"Fragnesia-go","owner":"Koshmare-Blossom","full_name":"Koshmare-Blossom/Fragnesia-go","html_url":"https://github.com/Koshmare-Blossom/Fragnesia-go","description":"A Go implementation of fragnesia (CVE-2026-46300)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":null,"created_at":"2026-05-20 20:24:02","updated_at":"2026-05-20 20:28:06","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 20:27:23","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 22:36:34","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1244473938","cve_id":"CVE-2026-43284","name":"Dirtyfrag-go","owner":"Koshmare-Blossom","full_name":"Koshmare-Blossom/Dirtyfrag-go","html_url":"https://github.com/Koshmare-Blossom/Dirtyfrag-go","description":"A Go implementation of dirtyfrag (CVE-2026-43284 / CVE-2026-43500)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"$3","created_at":"2026-05-20 18:49:06","updated_at":"2026-05-20 20:31:26","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 19:19:13","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 22:36:34","cvss_score":7.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244434638","cve_id":"CVE-2021-4034","name":"PwnKit-CVE-2021-4034","owner":"jayhutajulu1","full_name":"jayhutajulu1/PwnKit-CVE-2021-4034","html_url":"https://github.com/jayhutajulu1/PwnKit-CVE-2021-4034","description":"PoC for PwnKit / CVE-2021-4034 - Pkexec Local Privilege Escalation","stargazers_count":"1","vuln_description":"A local privilege escalation vulnerability was found on polkit's pkexec utility. The pkexec application is a setuid tool designed to allow unprivileged users to run commands as privileged users according predefined policies. The current version of pkexec doesn't handle the calling parameters count correctly and ends trying to execute environment variables as commands. An attacker can leverage this by crafting environment variables in such a way it'll induce pkexec to execute arbitrary code. When successfully executed the attack can cause a local privilege escalation given unprivileged users administrative rights on the target machine.","created_at":"2026-05-20 18:03:50","updated_at":"2026-05-20 18:13:23","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 18:10:41","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 22:36:31","cvss_score":7.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244420529","cve_id":"CVE-2026-45585","name":"Yellowkey-mitigation","owner":"bjbakker1984","full_name":"bjbakker1984/Yellowkey-mitigation","html_url":"https://github.com/bjbakker1984/Yellowkey-mitigation","description":"A small script to apply Yellowkey mitigation based on CVE-2026-45585 instructions","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Microsoft is aware of a security feature bypass vulnerability in Windows publicly referred to as &quot;YellowKey&quot;. The proof of concept for this vulnerability has been made public violating coordinated vulnerability best practices.\nWe are issuing this CVE to provide mitigation guidance that can be implemented to protect against this vulnerability until the security update is made available.","created_at":"2026-05-20 17:48:04","updated_at":"2026-05-20 20:40:27","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 20:40:24","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 22:36:34","cvss_score":6.8,"severity":"MEDIUM"},{"id":"1244389571","cve_id":"CVE-2026-31635","name":"CVE-2026-31635","owner":"Lutfifakee-Project","full_name":"Lutfifakee-Project/CVE-2026-31635","html_url":"https://github.com/Lutfifakee-Project/CVE-2026-31635","description":"Exploit for DirtyDecrypt - CVE-2026-31635 Local Privilege Escalation","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"$4","created_at":"2026-05-20 17:12:15","updated_at":"2026-05-20 17:14:49","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 17:14:45","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 22:36:34","cvss_score":7.5,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244381609","cve_id":"CVE-2026-0073","name":"CVE-2026-0073","owner":"0xbinder","full_name":"0xbinder/CVE-2026-0073","html_url":"https://github.com/0xbinder/CVE-2026-0073","description":"An automated exploit for CVE-2026-0073 (Android ADB TLS Auth Bypass). Features a built-in mDNS/Zeroconf scanner to instantly discover randomized Wireless Debugging ports on Android 13+ and establishes a fully interactive raw PTY shell.","stargazers_count":"4","vuln_description":"In adbd_tls_verify_cert of auth.cpp, there is a possible bypass of wireless ADB mutual authentication due to a logic error in the code. This could lead to remote (proximal/adjacent) code execution as the shell user with no additional execution privileges needed. User interaction is not needed for exploitation.","created_at":"2026-05-20 17:02:35","updated_at":"2026-05-20 21:30:02","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 19:53:30","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 22:36:33","cvss_score":8.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244361129","cve_id":"CVE-2026-42945","name":"CVE-2026-42945-NGINX-Rift-Toolkit","owner":"gagaltotal","full_name":"gagaltotal/CVE-2026-42945-NGINX-Rift-Toolkit","html_url":"https://github.com/gagaltotal/CVE-2026-42945-NGINX-Rift-Toolkit","description":"CVE-2026-42945 - NGINX Rift Toolkit","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"NGINX Plus and NGINX Open Source have a vulnerability in the ngx_http_rewrite_module module. This vulnerability exists when the rewrite directive is followed by a rewrite, if, or set directive and an unnamed Perl-Compatible Regular Expression (PCRE) capture (for example, $1, $2) with a replacement string that includes a question mark (?). An unauthenticated attacker along with conditions beyond its control can exploit this vulnerability by sending crafted HTTP requests. This may cause a heap buffer overflow in the NGINX worker process leading to a restart. Additionally, for systems with Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR ) disabled, code execution is possible.  Note: Software versions which have reached End of Technical Support (EoTS) are not evaluated.","created_at":"2026-05-20 16:37:58","updated_at":"2026-05-20 17:07:29","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 17:05:10","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 22:36:34","cvss_score":8.1,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244350875","cve_id":"CVE-2026-41651","name":"CVE-2026-41651","owner":"Lutfifakee-Project","full_name":"Lutfifakee-Project/CVE-2026-41651","html_url":"https://github.com/Lutfifakee-Project/CVE-2026-41651","description":"Exploit for CVE-2026-41651 - PackageKit TOCTOU Local Privilege Escalation (Pack2TheRoot)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"$5","created_at":"2026-05-20 16:26:05","updated_at":"2026-05-20 16:48:18","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 16:48:15","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 22:36:34","cvss_score":8.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244342979","cve_id":"CVE-2026-26980","name":"Ghost-CMS-Code-Injection-Audit-CVE-2026-26980","owner":"Kulik-Labs-Development","full_name":"Kulik-Labs-Development/Ghost-CMS-Code-Injection-Audit-CVE-2026-26980","html_url":"https://github.com/Kulik-Labs-Development/Ghost-CMS-Code-Injection-Audit-CVE-2026-26980","description":"Outdated Ghost CMS websites that have fallen become compromised from CVE-2026-26980 can suffer from spam code injection to pages. Use this to mass clear and edit code injection fields. ","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Ghost is a Node.js content management system. Versions 3.24.0 through 6.19.0 allow unauthenticated attackers to perform arbitrary reads from the database. This issue has been fixed in version 6.19.1.","created_at":"2026-05-20 16:16:41","updated_at":"2026-05-20 16:28:20","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 16:27:10","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 22:36:33","cvss_score":9.4,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1244270206","cve_id":"CVE-2023-29401","name":"gin-vulnerable","owner":"dannyEndorTest","full_name":"dannyEndorTest/gin-vulnerable","html_url":"https://github.com/dannyEndorTest/gin-vulnerable","description":"Demo consumer for gin v1.7.0 (CVE-2023-29401) — Context.FileAttachment with user input. endorctl scan target.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"The filename parameter of the Context.FileAttachment function is not properly sanitized. A maliciously crafted filename can cause the Content-Disposition header to be sent with an unexpected filename value or otherwise modify the Content-Disposition header. For example, a filename of \"setup.bat&quot;;x=.txt\" will be sent as a file named \"setup.bat\". If the FileAttachment function is called with names provided by an untrusted source, this may permit an attacker to cause a file to be served with a name different than provided. Maliciously crafted attachment file name can modify the Content-Disposition header.","created_at":"2026-05-20 14:45:18","updated_at":"2026-05-20 14:45:26","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 14:45:22","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 16:36:32","cvss_score":4.3,"severity":"MEDIUM"},{"id":"1244226886","cve_id":"CVE-2026-31431","name":"ptrace_may_dream","owner":"sgkdev","full_name":"sgkdev/ptrace_may_dream","html_url":"https://github.com/sgkdev/ptrace_may_dream","description":"CVE-2026-31431-killed page-cache exploit — code exec into containers sharing the same image layer","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ncrypto: algif_aead - Revert to operating out-of-place\n\nThis mostly reverts commit 72548b093ee3 except for the copying of\nthe associated data.\n\nThere is no benefit in operating in-place in algif_aead since the\nsource and destination come from different mappings.  Get rid of\nall the complexity added for in-place operation and just copy the\nAD directly.","created_at":"2026-05-20 13:37:35","updated_at":"2026-05-20 13:52:45","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 13:52:41","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 16:36:34","cvss_score":7.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244220931","cve_id":"CVE-2020-7602","name":"node-prompt-here","owner":"dannyEndorTest","full_name":"dannyEndorTest/node-prompt-here","html_url":"https://github.com/dannyEndorTest/node-prompt-here","description":"EXPOSURE demo target (node-prompt-here) — HOT baseline for CVE-2020-7602. See README.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"node-prompt-here through 1.0.1 allows execution of arbitrary commands. The \"runCommand()\" is called by \"getDevices()\" function in file \"linux/manager.js\", which is required by the \"index. process.env.NM_CLI\" in the file \"linux/manager.js\". This function is used to construct the argument of function \"execSync()\", which can be controlled by users without any sanitization.","created_at":"2026-05-20 13:27:16","updated_at":"2026-05-20 13:27:23","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 14:49:45","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 16:36:31","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1244220903","cve_id":"CVE-2021-23797","name":"http-server-node","owner":"dannyEndorTest","full_name":"dannyEndorTest/http-server-node","html_url":"https://github.com/dannyEndorTest/http-server-node","description":"EXPOSURE demo target (http-server-node) — HOT baseline for CVE-2021-23797. See README.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"All versions of package http-server-node are vulnerable to Directory Traversal via use of --path-as-is.","created_at":"2026-05-20 13:27:12","updated_at":"2026-05-20 13:27:19","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 14:49:49","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 16:36:31","cvss_score":7.5,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244219527","cve_id":"CVE-2026-35037","name":"POC_CVE-2026-35037","owner":"fineman999","full_name":"fineman999/POC_CVE-2026-35037","html_url":"https://github.com/fineman999/POC_CVE-2026-35037","description":"POC_CVE-2026-35037","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Ech0 is an open-source, self-hosted publishing platform for personal idea sharing. Prior to 4.2.8, the GET /api/website/title endpoint accepts an arbitrary URL via the website_url query parameter and makes a server-side HTTP request to it without any validation of the target host or IP address. The endpoint requires no authentication. An attacker can use this to reach internal network services, cloud metadata endpoints (169.254.169.254), and localhost-bound services, with partial response data exfiltrated via the HTML <title> tag extraction This vulnerability is fixed in 4.2.8.","created_at":"2026-05-20 13:24:58","updated_at":"2026-05-20 13:27:50","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 13:27:46","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 16:36:34","cvss_score":7.2,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244214987","cve_id":"CVE-2024-10821","name":"invokeai-consumer","owner":"dannyEndorTest","full_name":"dannyEndorTest/invokeai-consumer","html_url":"https://github.com/dannyEndorTest/invokeai-consumer","description":"Demo consumer for invokeai 5.0.1 (CVE-2024-10821; version named in CVE prose) — endorctl scan target","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A Denial of Service (DoS) vulnerability in the multipart request boundary processing mechanism of the Invoke-AI server (version v5.0.1) allows unauthenticated attackers to cause excessive resource consumption. The server fails to handle excessive characters appended to the end of multipart boundaries, leading to an infinite loop and a complete denial of service for all users. The affected endpoint is `/api/v1/images/upload`.","created_at":"2026-05-20 13:16:48","updated_at":"2026-05-20 13:16:55","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 13:16:51","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 16:36:32","cvss_score":7.5,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244214936","cve_id":"CVE-2024-12886","name":"ollama-consumer","owner":"dannyEndorTest","full_name":"dannyEndorTest/ollama-consumer","html_url":"https://github.com/dannyEndorTest/ollama-consumer","description":"Demo consumer for ollama v0.5.0 (vulnerable range for CVE-2024-12886) — endorctl scan target","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"An Out-Of-Memory (OOM) vulnerability exists in the `ollama` server version 0.3.14. This vulnerability can be triggered when a malicious API server responds with a gzip bomb HTTP response, leading to the `ollama` server crashing. The vulnerability is present in the `makeRequestWithRetry` and `getAuthorizationToken` functions, which use `io.ReadAll` to read the response body. This can result in excessive memory usage and a Denial of Service (DoS) condition.","created_at":"2026-05-20 13:16:43","updated_at":"2026-05-20 15:02:36","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 15:02:32","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 16:36:32","cvss_score":7.5,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244148568","cve_id":"CVE-2026-31635","name":"DirtyDecrypt","owner":"aexdyhaxor","full_name":"aexdyhaxor/DirtyDecrypt","html_url":"https://github.com/aexdyhaxor/DirtyDecrypt","description":"DirtyDecrypt PoC Released for Linux Kernel CVE-2026-31635 LPE Vulnerability","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"$6","created_at":"2026-05-20 11:22:12","updated_at":"2026-05-20 11:24:57","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 11:24:53","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 16:36:34","cvss_score":7.5,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244108480","cve_id":"CVE-2026-42271","name":"CVE-2026-42271-PoC","owner":"learner202649","full_name":"learner202649/CVE-2026-42271-PoC","html_url":"https://github.com/learner202649/CVE-2026-42271-PoC","description":"The code for personally reproducing the corresponding vulnerability","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"LiteLLM is a proxy server (AI Gateway) to call LLM APIs in OpenAI (or native) format. From version 1.74.2 to before version 1.83.7, two endpoints used to preview an MCP server before saving it — POST /mcp-rest/test/connection and POST /mcp-rest/test/tools/list — accepted a full server configuration in the request body, including the command, args, and env fields used by the stdio transport. When called with a stdio configuration, the endpoints attempted to connect, which spawned the supplied command as a subprocess on the proxy host with the privileges of the proxy process. The endpoints were gated only by a valid proxy API key, with no role check. Any authenticated user — including holders of low-privilege internal-user keys — could therefore run arbitrary commands on the host. This issue has been patched in version 1.83.7.","created_at":"2026-05-20 10:12:57","updated_at":"2026-05-20 10:13:40","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 10:13:35","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 16:36:34","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1244036325","cve_id":"CVE-2007-2447","name":"SMB-Penetration-Testing-NTLM-Relay-Version-2-","owner":"Youneskc","full_name":"Youneskc/SMB-Penetration-Testing-NTLM-Relay-Version-2-","html_url":"https://github.com/Youneskc/SMB-Penetration-Testing-NTLM-Relay-Version-2-","description":"SMB Red Team Lab— NTLM Relay via LLMNR Poisoning, CVE-2007-2447, NTLMv2 Hash Cracking & NT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM on Windows 10","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"The MS-RPC functionality in smbd in Samba 3.0.0 through 3.0.25rc3 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via shell metacharacters involving the (1) SamrChangePassword function, when the \"username map script\" smb.conf option is enabled, and allows remote authenticated users to execute commands via shell metacharacters involving other MS-RPC functions in the (2) remote printer and (3) file share management.","created_at":"2026-05-20 07:54:05","updated_at":"2026-05-20 08:11:28","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 08:11:23","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 10:36:29","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1244021635","cve_id":"CVE-2024-10821","name":"invokeai","owner":"dannyEndorTest","full_name":"dannyEndorTest/invokeai","html_url":"https://github.com/dannyEndorTest/invokeai","description":"EXPOSURE demo target (invokeai) — HOT baseline for CVE-2024-10821. See README.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A Denial of Service (DoS) vulnerability in the multipart request boundary processing mechanism of the Invoke-AI server (version v5.0.1) allows unauthenticated attackers to cause excessive resource consumption. The server fails to handle excessive characters appended to the end of multipart boundaries, leading to an infinite loop and a complete denial of service for all users. The affected endpoint is `/api/v1/images/upload`.","created_at":"2026-05-20 07:25:36","updated_at":"2026-05-20 07:25:42","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 07:36:03","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 10:36:33","cvss_score":7.5,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244021595","cve_id":"CVE-2024-12886","name":"ollama","owner":"dannyEndorTest","full_name":"dannyEndorTest/ollama","html_url":"https://github.com/dannyEndorTest/ollama","description":"EXPOSURE demo target (ollama) — HOT baseline for CVE-2024-12886. See README.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"An Out-Of-Memory (OOM) vulnerability exists in the `ollama` server version 0.3.14. This vulnerability can be triggered when a malicious API server responds with a gzip bomb HTTP response, leading to the `ollama` server crashing. The vulnerability is present in the `makeRequestWithRetry` and `getAuthorizationToken` functions, which use `io.ReadAll` to read the response body. This can result in excessive memory usage and a Denial of Service (DoS) condition.","created_at":"2026-05-20 07:25:32","updated_at":"2026-05-20 07:25:39","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 07:35:59","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 10:36:33","cvss_score":7.5,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1244021564","cve_id":"CVE-2018-15747","name":"glot-code-runner","owner":"dannyEndorTest","full_name":"dannyEndorTest/glot-code-runner","html_url":"https://github.com/dannyEndorTest/glot-code-runner","description":"EXPOSURE demo target (glot-code-runner) — HOT baseline for CVE-2018-15747. See README.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"The default configuration of glot-www through 2018-05-19 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code because glot-code-runner supports os.system within a \"python\" \"files\" \"content\" JSON file.","created_at":"2026-05-20 07:25:29","updated_at":"2026-05-20 07:25:35","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 07:35:48","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 10:36:30","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1244021534","cve_id":"CVE-2020-7602","name":"node-prompt-here","owner":"dannyEndorTest","full_name":"dannyEndorTest/node-prompt-here","html_url":"https://github.com/dannyEndorTest/node-prompt-here","description":"EXPOSURE demo target (node-prompt-here) — HOT baseline for CVE-2020-7602. See README.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"node-prompt-here through 1.0.1 allows execution of arbitrary commands. The \"runCommand()\" is called by \"getDevices()\" function in file \"linux/manager.js\", which is required by the \"index. process.env.NM_CLI\" in the file \"linux/manager.js\". This function is used to construct the argument of function \"execSync()\", which can be controlled by users without any sanitization.","created_at":"2026-05-20 07:25:25","updated_at":"2026-05-20 07:25:32","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 07:35:52","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 10:36:31","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1244021502","cve_id":"CVE-2021-23797","name":"http-server-node","owner":"dannyEndorTest","full_name":"dannyEndorTest/http-server-node","html_url":"https://github.com/dannyEndorTest/http-server-node","description":"EXPOSURE demo target (http-server-node) — HOT baseline for CVE-2021-23797. See README.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"All versions of package http-server-node are vulnerable to Directory Traversal via use of --path-as-is.","created_at":"2026-05-20 07:25:21","updated_at":"2026-05-20 07:25:28","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 07:35:55","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 10:36:31","cvss_score":7.5,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1243995135","cve_id":"CVE-2026-31635","name":"CVE-2026-31635","owner":"0xBlackash","full_name":"0xBlackash/CVE-2026-31635","html_url":"https://github.com/0xBlackash/CVE-2026-31635","description":"CVE-2026-31635","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"$7","created_at":"2026-05-20 06:39:31","updated_at":"2026-05-20 07:20:23","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 07:20:19","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 10:36:34","cvss_score":7.5,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1243980247","cve_id":"CVE-2024-37054","name":"CVE-2024-37054","owner":"tristanqtn","full_name":"tristanqtn/CVE-2024-37054","html_url":"https://github.com/tristanqtn/CVE-2024-37054","description":"CVE-2024-37054 exploit and documentation","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Deserialization of untrusted data can occur in versions of the MLflow platform running version 0.9.0 or newer, enabling a maliciously uploaded PyFunc model to run arbitrary code on an end user’s system when interacted with.","created_at":"2026-05-20 06:15:25","updated_at":"2026-05-20 07:00:40","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 07:00:36","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 10:36:33","cvss_score":8.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1243860313","cve_id":"CVE-2016-5195","name":"IoT-Firmware-Reverse-Engineering","owner":"SaanviShah30","full_name":"SaanviShah30/IoT-Firmware-Reverse-Engineering","html_url":"https://github.com/SaanviShah30/IoT-Firmware-Reverse-Engineering","description":"Reverse engineered IoT camera firmware and discovered CWE-78 command injection, DirtyCOW CVE-2016-5195, weak authentication and Telnet exposure | Binwalk IDA Pro Wireshark | University at Albany","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Race condition in mm/gup.c in the Linux kernel 2.x through 4.x before 4.8.3 allows local users to gain privileges by leveraging incorrect handling of a copy-on-write (COW) feature to write to a read-only memory mapping, as exploited in the wild in October 2016, aka \"Dirty COW.\"","created_at":"2026-05-20 03:28:47","updated_at":"2026-05-20 03:29:26","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 03:29:11","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 10:36:30","cvss_score":7,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1243842038","cve_id":"CVE-2026-42096","name":"sparx_hack","owner":"br0xpl","full_name":"br0xpl/sparx_hack","html_url":"https://github.com/br0xpl/sparx_hack","description":"Exploit code for CVE-2026-42096 and CVE-2026-42097 allowing for arbitrary SQL command execution without authentication.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Sparx Pro Cloud Server is vulnerable to Broken Access Control within communication with the database. Due to lack of permission checks, any low privileged user can run arbitrary SQL queries within database user context.\n\nThe vendor was notified early about this vulnerability, but didn't respond with the details of vulnerability or vulnerable version range. Only version 6.1 (build 167) and below were tested and confirmed as vulnerable, other versions were not tested and might also be vulnerable.","created_at":"2026-05-20 03:06:13","updated_at":"2026-05-20 03:19:56","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 03:19:51","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 04:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1243804602","cve_id":"CVE-2021-4034","name":"pwnkit_safety_check","owner":"vorkampfer","full_name":"vorkampfer/pwnkit_safety_check","html_url":"https://github.com/vorkampfer/pwnkit_safety_check","description":"PwnKit (CVE-2021-4034) Safe Checker This tool performs read-only checks and does not attempt exploitation. ","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A local privilege escalation vulnerability was found on polkit's pkexec utility. The pkexec application is a setuid tool designed to allow unprivileged users to run commands as privileged users according predefined policies. The current version of pkexec doesn't handle the calling parameters count correctly and ends trying to execute environment variables as commands. An attacker can leverage this by crafting environment variables in such a way it'll induce pkexec to execute arbitrary code. When successfully executed the attack can cause a local privilege escalation given unprivileged users administrative rights on the target machine.","created_at":"2026-05-20 02:21:07","updated_at":"2026-05-20 02:31:01","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 02:30:57","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 04:36:30","cvss_score":7.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1243756665","cve_id":"CVE-2026-45185","name":"POC_CVE-2026-45185","owner":"MJ-bin","full_name":"MJ-bin/POC_CVE-2026-45185","html_url":"https://github.com/MJ-bin/POC_CVE-2026-45185","description":"POC_CVE-2026-45185 for nuclei-templates","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Exim before 4.99.3, in certain GnuTLS configurations, has a remotely reachable use-after-free in the BDAT body parsing path. It is triggered when a client sends a TLS close_notify mid-body during a CHUNKING transfer, followed by a final cleartext byte on the same TCP connection. This can lead to heap corruption. An unauthenticated network attacker exploiting this vulnerability could execute arbitrary code.","created_at":"2026-05-20 01:26:55","updated_at":"2026-05-20 02:51:59","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 02:51:34","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 04:36:33","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1243753454","cve_id":"CVE-2017-0143","name":"thm-blue-writeup","owner":"FernandoTDalcin","full_name":"FernandoTDalcin/thm-blue-writeup","html_url":"https://github.com/FernandoTDalcin/thm-blue-writeup","description":"Writeup da sala Blue do TryHackMe — exploração do EternalBlue (MS17-010/CVE-2017-0143).","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"The SMBv1 server in Microsoft Windows Vista SP2; Windows Server 2008 SP2 and R2 SP1; Windows 7 SP1; Windows 8.1; Windows Server 2012 Gold and R2; Windows RT 8.1; and Windows 10 Gold, 1511, and 1607; and Windows Server 2016 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code via crafted packets, aka \"Windows SMB Remote Code Execution Vulnerability.\" This vulnerability is different from those described in CVE-2017-0144, CVE-2017-0145, CVE-2017-0146, and CVE-2017-0148.","created_at":"2026-05-20 01:23:07","updated_at":"2026-05-20 01:26:24","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 01:25:58","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 04:36:29","cvss_score":8.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1243745482","cve_id":"CVE-2026-42945","name":"CVE-2026-42945-NGINX-Rift-Scanner","owner":"gagaltotal","full_name":"gagaltotal/CVE-2026-42945-NGINX-Rift-Scanner","html_url":"https://github.com/gagaltotal/CVE-2026-42945-NGINX-Rift-Scanner","description":"NGINX Rift - CVE-2026-42945","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"NGINX Plus and NGINX Open Source have a vulnerability in the ngx_http_rewrite_module module. This vulnerability exists when the rewrite directive is followed by a rewrite, if, or set directive and an unnamed Perl-Compatible Regular Expression (PCRE) capture (for example, $1, $2) with a replacement string that includes a question mark (?). An unauthenticated attacker along with conditions beyond its control can exploit this vulnerability by sending crafted HTTP requests. This may cause a heap buffer overflow in the NGINX worker process leading to a restart. Additionally, for systems with Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR ) disabled, code execution is possible.  Note: Software versions which have reached End of Technical Support (EoTS) are not evaluated.","created_at":"2026-05-20 01:14:02","updated_at":"2026-05-20 01:15:10","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 01:14:03","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 04:36:33","cvss_score":8.1,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1243676586","cve_id":"CVE-2026-42945","name":"fix_nginx_cve_2026_42945","owner":"fkj-src","full_name":"fkj-src/fix_nginx_cve_2026_42945","html_url":"https://github.com/fkj-src/fix_nginx_cve_2026_42945","description":"NGINX CVE-2026-42945 一键修复脚本","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"NGINX Plus and NGINX Open Source have a vulnerability in the ngx_http_rewrite_module module. This vulnerability exists when the rewrite directive is followed by a rewrite, if, or set directive and an unnamed Perl-Compatible Regular Expression (PCRE) capture (for example, $1, $2) with a replacement string that includes a question mark (?). An unauthenticated attacker along with conditions beyond its control can exploit this vulnerability by sending crafted HTTP requests. This may cause a heap buffer overflow in the NGINX worker process leading to a restart. Additionally, for systems with Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR ) disabled, code execution is possible.  Note: Software versions which have reached End of Technical Support (EoTS) are not evaluated.","created_at":"2026-05-19 23:59:59","updated_at":"2026-05-20 03:18:53","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 03:02:56","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 04:36:33","cvss_score":8.1,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1243656264","cve_id":"CVE-2026-30691","name":"CVE-2026-30691","owner":"walidriouah","full_name":"walidriouah/CVE-2026-30691","html_url":"https://github.com/walidriouah/CVE-2026-30691","description":"CVE-2026-30691: Stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) in @cyntler/react-doc-viewer","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability in @cyntler/react-doc-viewer v1.17.1 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary JavaScript via a crafted .txt file. The TXTRenderer component fails to sanitize file content and explicitly casts raw data as a ReactNode","created_at":"2026-05-19 23:39:40","updated_at":"2026-05-20 00:23:19","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 00:06:51","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 04:36:33","cvss_score":6.1,"severity":"MEDIUM"},{"id":"1243618993","cve_id":"CVE-2026-35029","name":"CVE-2026-35029-PoC","owner":"learner202649","full_name":"learner202649/CVE-2026-35029-PoC","html_url":"https://github.com/learner202649/CVE-2026-35029-PoC","description":"The code for personally reproducing the corresponding vulnerability","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"LiteLLM is a proxy server (AI Gateway) to call LLM APIs in OpenAI (or native) format. Prior to 1.83.0, the /config/update endpoint does not enforce admin role authorization. A user who is already authenticated into the platform can then use this endpoint to modify proxy configuration and environment variables, register custom pass-through endpoint handlers pointing to attacker-controlled Python code, achieving remote code execution, read arbitrary server files by setting UI_LOGO_PATH and fetching via /get_image, and take over other privileged accounts by overwriting UI_USERNAME and UI_PASSWORD environment variables. Fixed in v1.83.0.","created_at":"2026-05-19 23:02:18","updated_at":"2026-05-19 23:11:20","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 23:04:12","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 04:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1243576091","cve_id":"CVE-2026-40217","name":"CVE-2026-40217-PoC","owner":"learner202649","full_name":"learner202649/CVE-2026-40217-PoC","html_url":"https://github.com/learner202649/CVE-2026-40217-PoC","description":"The code for personally reproducing the corresponding vulnerability","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"LiteLLM through 2026-04-08 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code via bytecode rewriting at the /guardrails/test_custom_code URI.","created_at":"2026-05-19 22:19:42","updated_at":"2026-05-19 22:23:44","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 22:20:16","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 04:36:33","cvss_score":8.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1243514498","cve_id":"CVE-2026-35030","name":"CVE-2026-35030-PoC","owner":"learner202649","full_name":"learner202649/CVE-2026-35030-PoC","html_url":"https://github.com/learner202649/CVE-2026-35030-PoC","description":"The code for personally reproducing the corresponding vulnerability","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"LiteLLM is a proxy server (AI Gateway) to call LLM APIs in OpenAI (or native) format. Prior to 1.83.0, when JWT authentication is enabled (enable_jwt_auth: true), the OIDC userinfo cache uses token[:20] as the cache key. JWT headers produced by the same signing algorithm generate identical first 20 characters. This configuration option is not enabled by default. Most instances are not affected. An unauthenticated attacker can craft a token whose first 20 characters match a legitimate user's cached token. On cache hit, the attacker inherits the legitimate user's identity and permissions. This affects deployments with JWT/OIDC authentication enabled. Fixed in v1.83.0.","created_at":"2026-05-19 21:13:16","updated_at":"2026-05-19 21:16:09","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 21:16:05","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 22:36:34","cvss_score":9.1,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1243474111","cve_id":"CVE-2021-21735","name":"cve-2021-21735-zte-zxhn-h168n-admin-compromise","owner":"minanagehsalalma","full_name":"minanagehsalalma/cve-2021-21735-zte-zxhn-h168n-admin-compromise","html_url":"https://github.com/minanagehsalalma/cve-2021-21735-zte-zxhn-h168n-admin-compromise","description":"CVE-2021-21735 write-up: ZTE ZXHN H168N V3.5 wizard-page information leak, firmware routing flaw, and the path from exposed PPPoE/WLAN data to full admin compromise.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A ZTE product has an information leak vulnerability. Due to improper permission settings, an attacker with ordinary user permissions could exploit this vulnerability to obtain some sensitive user information through the wizard page without authentication. This affects ZXHN H168N all versions up to V3.5.0_EG1T4_TE.","created_at":"2026-05-19 20:26:32","updated_at":"2026-05-20 22:41:15","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 22:35:44","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 04:36:31","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1243470366","cve_id":"CVE-2021-35036","name":"zyxel-cve-2021-35036-super-admin-password-leak","owner":"minanagehsalalma","full_name":"minanagehsalalma/zyxel-cve-2021-35036-super-admin-password-leak","html_url":"https://github.com/minanagehsalalma/zyxel-cve-2021-35036-super-admin-password-leak","description":"Deep-dive write-up for CVE-2021-35036, plus an adapted VMG8825-B50B genpass lab showing how Zyxel super-admin, TR-069, and FTPS credentials could be exposed across shared firmware.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A cleartext storage of information vulnerability in the Zyxel VMG3625-T50B firmware version V5.50(ABTL.0)b2k could allow an authenticated attacker to obtain sensitive information from the configuration file.","created_at":"2026-05-19 20:22:20","updated_at":"2026-05-20 23:12:45","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 23:06:20","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 04:36:31","cvss_score":6.5,"severity":"MEDIUM"},{"id":"1243469465","cve_id":"CVE-2026-34474","name":"cve-2026-34474-zte-h298a-h108n-sensitive-data-exposure","owner":"minanagehsalalma","full_name":"minanagehsalalma/cve-2026-34474-zte-h298a-h108n-sensitive-data-exposure","html_url":"https://github.com/minanagehsalalma/cve-2026-34474-zte-h298a-h108n-sensitive-data-exposure","description":"CVE-2026-34474: unauthenticated ETHCheat=1 requests leak the admin password and Wi-Fi PSK from ZTE H298A/H108N routers.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Sensitive data exposure leading to admin/WLAN credential leak in ZTE ZXHN H298A 1.1 and H108N 2.6. A crafted request to the router web interface can expose sensitive device and account information. In affected builds, the response may include the administrator password and WLAN PSK, enabling authentication bypass and network compromise. Some firmware versions may expose only partial identifiers (e.g., serial number, ESSID, MAC addresses).","created_at":"2026-05-19 20:21:19","updated_at":"2026-05-20 22:20:34","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 22:20:14","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 04:36:33","cvss_score":7.5,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1243460773","cve_id":"CVE-2024-21490","name":"roninforge-angularjs-migration","owner":"RoninForge","full_name":"RoninForge/roninforge-angularjs-migration","html_url":"https://github.com/RoninForge/roninforge-angularjs-migration","description":"AngularJS 1.x -> Angular 18 migration guidance for GitHub Copilot. Source-of-truth repo for github/awesome-copilot/instructions/angularjs-to-angular-18.instructions.md. 62 LLM regressions across 3 modes. AngularJS EOL since Dec 31 2021; CVE-2024-21490 unpatched.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"This affects versions of the package angular from 1.3.0. A regular expression used to split the value of the ng-srcset directive is vulnerable to super-linear runtime due to backtracking. With large carefully-crafted input, this can result in catastrophic backtracking and cause a denial of service. \r\r\r**Note:**\r\rThis package is EOL and will not receive any updates to address this issue. Users should migrate to [@angular/core](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@angular/core).","created_at":"2026-05-19 20:11:09","updated_at":"2026-05-19 20:11:20","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 20:11:16","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 22:36:32","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1243457978","cve_id":"CVE-2026-43284","name":"Dirty-Frag-CVE-2026-43284","owner":"kuniyal08","full_name":"kuniyal08/Dirty-Frag-CVE-2026-43284","html_url":"https://github.com/kuniyal08/Dirty-Frag-CVE-2026-43284","description":"A report on Dirty Frag, which is a Linux Local Privilege Escalation (LPE) vulnerability chain that allows an unprivileged user to gain root access","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"$8","created_at":"2026-05-19 20:07:42","updated_at":"2026-05-19 20:20:02","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 20:19:59","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 22:36:34","cvss_score":7.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1243423282","cve_id":"CVE-2025-59139","name":"roninforge-hono","owner":"RoninForge","full_name":"RoninForge/roninforge-hono","html_url":"https://github.com/RoninForge/roninforge-hono","description":"Cursor plugin for Hono v4 (TypeScript edge web framework). 59 LLM regressions with BAD/CORRECT pairs. Pinned to hono ^4.12.19 (>= 4.9.7 for CVE-2025-59139). Covers Express middleware leakage, v3-era removed APIs, RPC inference traps, Cloudflare Workers gotchas, security defaults, JSX SSR hardening.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"$9","created_at":"2026-05-19 19:25:45","updated_at":"2026-05-19 19:26:01","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 19:26:29","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 22:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1243409686","cve_id":"CVE-2024-23222","name":"webkit-cve-2024-23222","owner":"Umit-MHL","full_name":"Umit-MHL/webkit-cve-2024-23222","html_url":"https://github.com/Umit-MHL/webkit-cve-2024-23222","description":"CVE-2024-23222 WebKit type confusion → iOS 16.4.1 sandbox escape. Full chain: JSC JIT confusion → addrof/read64/write64 → WASM indirect call → arbitrary C functions → file write outside sandbox.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A type confusion issue was addressed with improved checks. This issue is fixed in iOS 17.3 and iPadOS 17.3, macOS Sonoma 14.3, tvOS 17.3. Processing maliciously crafted web content may lead to arbitrary code execution. Apple is aware of a report that this issue may have been exploited.","created_at":"2026-05-19 19:09:50","updated_at":"2026-05-19 20:14:44","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 20:14:40","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 22:36:32","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1243354056","cve_id":"CVE-2026-31431","name":"cve-2026-31431-checker","owner":"GubiczaP","full_name":"GubiczaP/cve-2026-31431-checker","html_url":"https://github.com/GubiczaP/cve-2026-31431-checker","description":"Shell scanner for CVE-2026-31431 \"Copy Fail\" — a local privilege escalation via Linux kernel page cache corruption (algif_aead/AF_ALG). Checks kernel version, patch status, module state, setuid exposure and mitigations. Supports Debian 11–13 and Ubuntu 20.04–25.10. CI/CD-ready (exit codes + JSON output).","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ncrypto: algif_aead - Revert to operating out-of-place\n\nThis mostly reverts commit 72548b093ee3 except for the copying of\nthe associated data.\n\nThere is no benefit in operating in-place in algif_aead since the\nsource and destination come from different mappings.  Get rid of\nall the complexity added for in-place operation and just copy the\nAD directly.","created_at":"2026-05-19 18:07:59","updated_at":"2026-05-19 18:13:17","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 18:13:13","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 22:36:34","cvss_score":7.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1243300748","cve_id":"CVE-2023-32692","name":"CVE-2023-32692-CodeIgniter4","owner":"mogwailabs","full_name":"mogwailabs/CVE-2023-32692-CodeIgniter4","html_url":"https://github.com/mogwailabs/CVE-2023-32692-CodeIgniter4","description":"Example application, vulnerable to CVE-2023-32692 (Validation Rule Injection in the PHP Framework CodeIgniter)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"CodeIgniter is a PHP full-stack web framework. This vulnerability allows attackers to execute arbitrary code when you use Validation Placeholders. The vulnerability exists in the Validation library, and validation methods in the controller and in-model validation are also vulnerable because they use the Validation library internally. This issue is patched in version 4.3.5.\n","created_at":"2026-05-19 17:08:43","updated_at":"2026-05-19 17:09:26","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 17:09:21","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 22:36:32","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1243300248","cve_id":"CVE-2026-35029","name":"CVE-2026-35029-PoC","owner":"learner202649","full_name":"learner202649/CVE-2026-35029-PoC","html_url":"https://github.com/learner202649/CVE-2026-35029-PoC","description":"The code for personally reproducing the corresponding vulnerability","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"LiteLLM is a proxy server (AI Gateway) to call LLM APIs in OpenAI (or native) format. Prior to 1.83.0, the /config/update endpoint does not enforce admin role authorization. A user who is already authenticated into the platform can then use this endpoint to modify proxy configuration and environment variables, register custom pass-through endpoint handlers pointing to attacker-controlled Python code, achieving remote code execution, read arbitrary server files by setting UI_LOGO_PATH and fetching via /get_image, and take over other privileged accounts by overwriting UI_USERNAME and UI_PASSWORD environment variables. Fixed in v1.83.0.","created_at":"2026-05-19 17:08:06","updated_at":"2026-05-19 17:09:50","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 17:09:45","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 22:36:34","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1243282205","cve_id":"CVE-2025-55182","name":"CVE-2025-55182-React2Shell","owner":"Industri4l-H3ll-Xpl0it3rs","full_name":"Industri4l-H3ll-Xpl0it3rs/CVE-2025-55182-React2Shell","html_url":"https://github.com/Industri4l-H3ll-Xpl0it3rs/CVE-2025-55182-React2Shell","description":" CVE-2025-55182 Exploit | by infrar3d","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A pre-authentication remote code execution vulnerability exists in React Server Components versions 19.0.0, 19.1.0, 19.1.1, and 19.2.0 including the following packages: react-server-dom-parcel, react-server-dom-turbopack, and react-server-dom-webpack. The vulnerable code unsafely deserializes payloads from HTTP requests to Server Function endpoints.","created_at":"2026-05-19 16:47:32","updated_at":"2026-05-19 19:33:31","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 17:06:46","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 22:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1243238310","cve_id":"CVE-2024-36420","name":"POC_CVE-2024-36420","owner":"fineman999","full_name":"fineman999/POC_CVE-2024-36420","html_url":"https://github.com/fineman999/POC_CVE-2024-36420","description":"POC_CVE-2024-36420","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Flowise is a drag & drop user interface to build a customized large language model flow. In version 1.4.3 of Flowise, the `/api/v1/openai-assistants-file` endpoint in `index.ts` is vulnerable to arbitrary file read due to lack of sanitization of the `fileName` body parameter. No known patches for this issue are available.","created_at":"2026-05-19 15:56:35","updated_at":"2026-05-19 16:07:39","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 16:07:35","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 22:36:32","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1243088466","cve_id":"CVE-2025-45809","name":"CVE-2025-45809-PoC","owner":"learner202649","full_name":"learner202649/CVE-2025-45809-PoC","html_url":"https://github.com/learner202649/CVE-2025-45809-PoC","description":"The code for personally reproducing the corresponding vulnerability","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"SQL Injection vulnerability in BerriAI LiteLLM before 1.81.0 allows attackers to execute arbitrary commands via the key parameter to the \"/key/block\" and \"/key/unblock\" API endpoints.","created_at":"2026-05-19 12:21:37","updated_at":"2026-05-19 12:27:28","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 12:27:24","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 16:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1243045131","cve_id":"CVE-2024-37032","name":"CVE-2024-37032-PoC","owner":"itzSh4dowxZ","full_name":"itzSh4dowxZ/CVE-2024-37032-PoC","html_url":"https://github.com/itzSh4dowxZ/CVE-2024-37032-PoC","description":"PoC for CVE-2024-37032 (Probllama): Ollama <=0.1.33 path traversal/arbitrary file write via model digest handling, using a FastAPI rogue registry, connector workflow, and shared object preload demo for authorized lab testing.","stargazers_count":"6","vuln_description":"Ollama before 0.1.34 does not validate the format of the digest (sha256 with 64 hex digits) when getting the model path, and thus mishandles the TestGetBlobsPath test cases such as fewer than 64 hex digits, more than 64 hex digits, or an initial ../ substring.","created_at":"2026-05-19 11:10:28","updated_at":"2026-05-19 14:52:23","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 14:19:58","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 16:36:32","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1243027261","cve_id":"CVE-2025-11203","name":"CVE-2025-11203-PoC","owner":"learner202649","full_name":"learner202649/CVE-2025-11203-PoC","html_url":"https://github.com/learner202649/CVE-2025-11203-PoC","description":"The code for personally reproducing the corresponding vulnerability","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"LiteLLM Information health API_KEY Information Disclosure Vulnerability. This vulnerability allows remote attackers to disclose sensitive information on affected installations of LiteLLM. Authentication is required to exploit this vulnerability.\n\nThe specific flaw exists within the handling of the API_KEY parameter provided to the health endpoint. The issue results from exposing sensitive information to an unauthorized actor. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to disclose stored credentials, leading to further compromise. Was ZDI-CAN-26585.","created_at":"2026-05-19 10:39:07","updated_at":"2026-05-19 12:35:50","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 12:35:47","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 16:36:32","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1243006856","cve_id":"CVE-2026-43284","name":"CVE-2026-43284","owner":"LucasPDiniz","full_name":"LucasPDiniz/CVE-2026-43284","html_url":"https://github.com/LucasPDiniz/CVE-2026-43284","description":"Dirty Frag - kernel Linux critical Vulnerability","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"$a","created_at":"2026-05-19 10:02:36","updated_at":"2026-05-19 10:06:45","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 10:05:25","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 16:36:33","cvss_score":7.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1242816604","cve_id":"CVE-2026-43500","name":"CVE-2026-43500","owner":"First-John","full_name":"First-John/CVE-2026-43500","html_url":"https://github.com/First-John/CVE-2026-43500","description":"CVE-2026-43500 / CVE-2026-31431 / CVE-2026-43284 golang hotfix","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nrxrpc: Also unshare DATA/RESPONSE packets when paged frags are present\n\nThe DATA-packet handler in rxrpc_input_call_event() and the RESPONSE\nhandler in rxrpc_verify_response() copy the skb to a linear one before\ncalling into the security ops only when skb_cloned() is true.  An skb\nthat is not cloned but still carries externally-owned paged fragments\n(e.g. SKBFL_SHARED_FRAG set by splice() into a UDP socket via\n__ip_append_data, or a chained skb_has_frag_list()) falls through to\nthe in-place decryption path, which binds the frag pages directly into\nthe AEAD/skcipher SGL via skb_to_sgvec().\n\nExtend the gate to also unshare when skb_has_frag_list() or\nskb_has_shared_frag() is true.  This catches the splice-loopback vector\nand other externally-shared frag sources while preserving the\nzero-copy fast path for skbs whose frags are kernel-private (e.g. NIC\npage_pool RX, GRO).  The OOM/trace handling already in place is reused.","created_at":"2026-05-19 04:32:29","updated_at":"2026-05-19 05:17:02","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 04:43:27","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 10:36:34","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1242816393","cve_id":"CVE-2026-31431","name":"cve-2026-31431-mitigation","owner":"Yakovyakov","full_name":"Yakovyakov/cve-2026-31431-mitigation","html_url":"https://github.com/Yakovyakov/cve-2026-31431-mitigation","description":"    Detection and mitigation tooling for CVE-2026-31431 (Copy Fail) on Linux kernels. Includes Phalanx-CCS and Silent4Labs scripts plus an Ansible playbook to apply temporary mitigation (block algif_aead module or boot parameter) across servers.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ncrypto: algif_aead - Revert to operating out-of-place\n\nThis mostly reverts commit 72548b093ee3 except for the copying of\nthe associated data.\n\nThere is no benefit in operating in-place in algif_aead since the\nsource and destination come from different mappings.  Get rid of\nall the complexity added for in-place operation and just copy the\nAD directly.","created_at":"2026-05-19 04:32:12","updated_at":"2026-05-19 04:32:13","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 04:32:13","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 10:36:34","cvss_score":7.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1242713248","cve_id":"CVE-2024-32019","name":"Exploit-CVE-2024-32019","owner":"Akira07210","full_name":"Akira07210/Exploit-CVE-2024-32019","html_url":"https://github.com/Akira07210/Exploit-CVE-2024-32019","description":"Script exploit the CVE-2024-32019. Credit to froxlor for the vuln.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Netdata is an open source observability tool. In affected versions the `ndsudo` tool shipped with affected versions of the Netdata Agent allows an attacker to run arbitrary programs with root permissions. The `ndsudo` tool is packaged as a `root`-owned executable with the SUID bit set. It only runs a restricted set of external commands, but its search paths are supplied by the `PATH` environment variable. This allows an attacker to control where `ndsudo` looks for these commands, which may be a path the attacker has write access to. This may lead to local privilege escalation. This vulnerability has been addressed in versions 1.45.3 and 1.45.2-169. Users are advised to upgrade. There are no known workarounds for this vulnerability.","created_at":"2026-05-19 02:23:39","updated_at":"2026-05-19 02:52:52","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 02:52:49","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 04:36:32","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1242665975","cve_id":"CVE-2026-33825","name":"CVE-2026-33825","owner":"0xBlackash","full_name":"0xBlackash/CVE-2026-33825","html_url":"https://github.com/0xBlackash/CVE-2026-33825","description":"CVE-2026-33825","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Insufficient granularity of access control in Microsoft Defender allows an authorized attacker to elevate privileges locally.","created_at":"2026-05-19 01:28:47","updated_at":"2026-05-19 01:52:38","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 01:52:35","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 04:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1242659504","cve_id":"CVE-2025-55182","name":"CVE-2025-55182","owner":"ycseo-git","full_name":"ycseo-git/CVE-2025-55182","html_url":"https://github.com/ycseo-git/CVE-2025-55182","description":"a.k.a. React2Shell","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A pre-authentication remote code execution vulnerability exists in React Server Components versions 19.0.0, 19.1.0, 19.1.1, and 19.2.0 including the following packages: react-server-dom-parcel, react-server-dom-turbopack, and react-server-dom-webpack. The vulnerable code unsafely deserializes payloads from HTTP requests to Server Function endpoints.","created_at":"2026-05-19 01:21:30","updated_at":"2026-05-19 03:20:44","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 03:20:40","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 04:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1242619437","cve_id":"CVE-2026-34472","name":"cve-2026-34472-auth-bypass-zte-h188a-router","owner":"minanagehsalalma","full_name":"minanagehsalalma/cve-2026-34472-auth-bypass-zte-h188a-router","html_url":"https://github.com/minanagehsalalma/cve-2026-34472-auth-bypass-zte-h188a-router","description":"Technical breakdown of CVE-2026-34472, an auth bypass via leaked credentials affecting ZTE H188A routers.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Unauthenticated credential disclosure in the wizard interface in ZTE ZXHN H188A V6.0.10P2_TE and V6.0.10P3N3_TE allows unauthenticated attackers on the local network to retrieve sensitive credentials from the router's web management interface, including the default administrator password, WLAN PSK, and PPPoE credentials. In some observed cases, configuration changes may also be performed without authentication.","created_at":"2026-05-19 00:37:38","updated_at":"2026-05-20 21:12:04","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 20:18:26","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 22:36:34","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1242618342","cve_id":"CVE-2020-17103","name":"MiniPlasma-Runner","owner":"AlexLinov","full_name":"AlexLinov/MiniPlasma-Runner","html_url":"https://github.com/AlexLinov/MiniPlasma-Runner","description":"CVE-2020-17103 adapted for C2 with split-binary SYSTEM callback","stargazers_count":"2","vuln_description":"Windows Cloud Files Mini Filter Driver Elevation of Privilege Vulnerability","created_at":"2026-05-19 00:36:34","updated_at":"2026-05-21 00:13:08","pushed_at":"2026-05-20 22:07:06","inserted_at":"2026-05-21 04:36:31","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1242508964","cve_id":"CVE-2026-33824","name":"IKEV2-POC","owner":"EpSiLoNPoInTOrI","full_name":"EpSiLoNPoInTOrI/IKEV2-POC","html_url":"https://github.com/EpSiLoNPoInTOrI/IKEV2-POC","description":"IKEv2, ikeext.dll, CVE-2026-33824, double free, heap grooming, ROP, SKF fragmentation, Windows exploit, anti-debug, obfuscation, API hooking, shellcode, reverse shell","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Double free in Windows IKE Extension allows an unauthorized attacker to execute code over a network.","created_at":"2026-05-18 22:44:31","updated_at":"2026-05-18 22:45:23","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 22:45:09","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 04:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1242455081","cve_id":"CVE-2024-27198","name":"CVE-2024-27198_Lab","owner":"cmpnn-romain","full_name":"cmpnn-romain/CVE-2024-27198_Lab","html_url":"https://github.com/cmpnn-romain/CVE-2024-27198_Lab","description":"Lab for the CVE-2024-27198","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"In JetBrains TeamCity before 2023.11.4 authentication bypass allowing to perform admin actions was possible","created_at":"2026-05-18 21:49:39","updated_at":"2026-05-20 17:03:40","pushed_at":"2026-05-19 00:02:54","inserted_at":"2026-05-20 22:36:32","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1242442844","cve_id":"CVE-2020-17103","name":"MiniPlasma-Detection","owner":"arch1m3d","full_name":"arch1m3d/MiniPlasma-Detection","html_url":"https://github.com/arch1m3d/MiniPlasma-Detection","description":"Sigma detection rule for MiniPlasma (CVE-2020-17103)","stargazers_count":"1","vuln_description":"Windows Cloud Files Mini Filter Driver Elevation of Privilege Vulnerability","created_at":"2026-05-18 21:36:51","updated_at":"2026-05-19 02:58:02","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 21:40:13","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 04:36:30","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1242433002","cve_id":"CVE-2025-34291","name":"CVE-2025-34291_cors_security_scanner","owner":"amnnrth","full_name":"amnnrth/CVE-2025-34291_cors_security_scanner","html_url":"https://github.com/amnnrth/CVE-2025-34291_cors_security_scanner","description":"A lightweight Python-based security assessment tool for detecting dangerous Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) misconfigurations - CVE-2025-34291.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Langflow versions up to and including 1.6.9 contain a chained vulnerability that enables account takeover and remote code execution. An overly permissive CORS configuration (allow_origins='*' with allow_credentials=True) combined with a refresh token cookie configured as SameSite=None allows a malicious webpage to perform cross-origin requests that include credentials and successfully call the refresh endpoint. An attacker-controlled origin can therefore obtain fresh access_token / refresh_token pairs for a victim session. Obtained tokens permit access to authenticated endpoints — including built-in code-execution functionality — allowing the attacker to execute arbitrary code and achieve full system compromise.","created_at":"2026-05-18 21:26:03","updated_at":"2026-05-18 21:29:04","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 21:29:00","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 04:36:32","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1242351939","cve_id":"CVE-2026-0596","name":"CVE-2026-0596-Reproduction","owner":"SparshBiswas-AI","full_name":"SparshBiswas-AI/CVE-2026-0596-Reproduction","html_url":"https://github.com/SparshBiswas-AI/CVE-2026-0596-Reproduction","description":"Research environment and validation scripts for evaluating deserialization behaviors in MLflow and MLServer.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A command injection vulnerability exists in mlflow/mlflow when serving a model with `enable_mlserver=True`. The `model_uri` is embedded directly into a shell command executed via `bash -c` without proper sanitization. If the `model_uri` contains shell metacharacters, such as `$()` or backticks, it allows for command substitution and execution of attacker-controlled commands. This vulnerability affects the latest version of mlflow/mlflow and can lead to privilege escalation if a higher-privileged service serves models from a directory writable by lower-privileged users.","created_at":"2026-05-18 19:53:46","updated_at":"2026-05-18 20:16:45","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 20:16:41","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 04:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1242306496","cve_id":"CVE-2025-14177","name":"CVE-2025-14177","owner":"34zY","full_name":"34zY/CVE-2025-14177","html_url":"https://github.com/34zY/CVE-2025-14177","description":"PHP getimagesize() CVE-2025-14177 - Heap Memory Leak Exploit Generator Fully functional exploit chain in Python","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"In PHP versions:8.1.* before 8.1.34, 8.2.* before 8.2.30, 8.3.* before 8.3.29, 8.4.* before 8.4.16, 8.5.* before 8.5.1, the getimagesize() function may leak uninitialized heap memory into the APPn segments (e.g., APP1) when reading images in multi-chunk mode (such as via php://filter). This occurs due to a bug in php_read_stream_all_chunks() that overwrites the buffer without advancing the pointer, leaving tail bytes uninitialized. This may lead to information disclosure of sensitive heap data and affect the confidentiality of the target server.","created_at":"2026-05-18 19:00:32","updated_at":"2026-05-18 19:05:44","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 19:05:40","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 04:36:32","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1242279173","cve_id":"CVE-2026-8053","name":"CVE-2026-8053-MongoDB","owner":"mgiay","full_name":"mgiay/CVE-2026-8053-MongoDB","html_url":"https://github.com/mgiay/CVE-2026-8053-MongoDB","description":"Desc \"CVE-2026-8053 CHECKER\"-20260518-16h30-GMT+7","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"An issue in MongoDB Server's time-series collection implementation allows an authenticated user with database write privileges to trigger an out-of-bounds memory write in the mongod process. The issue results from an inconsistency in the internal field-name-to-index mapping within the time-series bucket catalog. Under certain conditions this can result in arbitrary code execution.\n\nThis issue impacts MongoDB Server v5.0 versions prior to 5.0.33, v6.0 versions prior to 6.0.28, v7.0 versions prior to 7.0.34, v8.0 versions prior to 8.0.23, v8.2 versions prior to 8.2.9 and v8.3 versions prior to 8.3.2.","created_at":"2026-05-18 18:29:52","updated_at":"2026-05-18 23:37:38","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 23:37:22","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 04:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1242267233","cve_id":"CVE-2026-45321","name":"tanscript-exploit-check","owner":"nkopylov","full_name":"nkopylov/tanscript-exploit-check","html_url":"https://github.com/nkopylov/tanscript-exploit-check","description":"IOC checker for the TanStack/Mini Shai-Hulud npm supply chain attack (CVE-2026-45321)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"On 2026-05-11, between approximately 19:20 and 19:26 UTC, 84 malicious versions across 42 @tanstack/* packages were published to the npm registry. The publishes were authenticated via the legitimate GitHub Actions OIDC trusted-publisher binding for TanStack/router, but the publish workflow itself was not modified. The attacker chained three known vulnerability classes — a pull_request_target \"Pwn Request\" misconfiguration, GitHub Actions cache poisoning across the fork↔base trust boundary, and runtime memory extraction of the OIDC token from the Actions runner process — to publish credential-stealing malware under a trusted identity. Each affected package received exactly two malicious versions, published a few minutes apart.","created_at":"2026-05-18 18:16:47","updated_at":"2026-05-18 18:24:43","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 18:24:39","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 04:36:33","cvss_score":9.6,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1242185450","cve_id":"CVE-2026-31431","name":"CVE-2026-31431","owner":"royayub","full_name":"royayub/CVE-2026-31431","html_url":"https://github.com/royayub/CVE-2026-31431","description":"Local Privilege Escalation. Flips the running user's UID to 0 in /etc/passwd's page cache, then invokes su for a root shell.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ncrypto: algif_aead - Revert to operating out-of-place\n\nThis mostly reverts commit 72548b093ee3 except for the copying of\nthe associated data.\n\nThere is no benefit in operating in-place in algif_aead since the\nsource and destination come from different mappings.  Get rid of\nall the complexity added for in-place operation and just copy the\nAD directly.","created_at":"2026-05-18 16:44:05","updated_at":"2026-05-18 16:50:50","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 16:50:46","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 04:36:33","cvss_score":7.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1242168928","cve_id":"CVE-2021-4034","name":"PwnKit-","owner":"trinetra-1308","full_name":"trinetra-1308/PwnKit-","html_url":"https://github.com/trinetra-1308/PwnKit-","description":"This repository provides proof of concept (PoC) for the CVE-2021-4034","stargazers_count":"1","vuln_description":"A local privilege escalation vulnerability was found on polkit's pkexec utility. The pkexec application is a setuid tool designed to allow unprivileged users to run commands as privileged users according predefined policies. The current version of pkexec doesn't handle the calling parameters count correctly and ends trying to execute environment variables as commands. An attacker can leverage this by crafting environment variables in such a way it'll induce pkexec to execute arbitrary code. When successfully executed the attack can cause a local privilege escalation given unprivileged users administrative rights on the target machine.","created_at":"2026-05-18 16:26:55","updated_at":"2026-05-18 19:29:30","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 19:29:26","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 04:36:30","cvss_score":7.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1242142526","cve_id":"CVE-2026-39636","name":"CVE-2026-39636-vulnerability-exp","owner":"CatchCatOoO","full_name":"CatchCatOoO/CVE-2026-39636-vulnerability-exp","html_url":"https://github.com/CatchCatOoO/CVE-2026-39636-vulnerability-exp","description":"暂无","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting') vulnerability in livemesh Livemesh Addons for Elementor addons-for-elementor allows Stored XSS.This issue affects Livemesh Addons for Elementor: from n/a through <= 9.0.","created_at":"2026-05-18 16:01:22","updated_at":"2026-05-18 16:28:26","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 16:28:22","inserted_at":"2026-05-19 04:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1242068559","cve_id":"CVE-2026-31431","name":"CVE-2026-31431-CopyFail","owner":"4xura","full_name":"4xura/CVE-2026-31431-CopyFail","html_url":"https://github.com/4xura/CVE-2026-31431-CopyFail","description":"A repository that stores artifacts, exploit scripts for the writeup at https://4xura.com , targeting the Linux LPE named \"Copy Fail\"","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ncrypto: algif_aead - Revert to operating out-of-place\n\nThis mostly reverts commit 72548b093ee3 except for the copying of\nthe associated data.\n\nThere is no benefit in operating in-place in algif_aead since the\nsource and destination come from different mappings.  Get rid of\nall the complexity added for in-place operation and just copy the\nAD directly.","created_at":"2026-05-18 14:23:15","updated_at":"2026-05-18 15:31:21","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 15:31:17","inserted_at":"2026-05-18 16:36:33","cvss_score":7.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1241989925","cve_id":"CVE-2017-5638","name":"apache-struts-cve-2017-5638-project","owner":"Majaktech","full_name":"Majaktech/apache-struts-cve-2017-5638-project","html_url":"https://github.com/Majaktech/apache-struts-cve-2017-5638-project","description":"Attack and Defense course project focused on CVE-2017-5638 analysis, exploitation, and mitigation.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"The Jakarta Multipart parser in Apache Struts 2 2.3.x before 2.3.32 and 2.5.x before 2.5.10.1 has incorrect exception handling and error-message generation during file-upload attempts, which allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted Content-Type, Content-Disposition, or Content-Length HTTP header, as exploited in the wild in March 2017 with a Content-Type header containing a #cmd= string.","created_at":"2026-05-18 12:09:35","updated_at":"2026-05-18 12:14:49","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 12:14:45","inserted_at":"2026-05-18 16:36:29","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1241917963","cve_id":"CVE-2021-44228","name":"mi-laboratorio-log4shell","owner":"MAFO-sec","full_name":"MAFO-sec/mi-laboratorio-log4shell","html_url":"https://github.com/MAFO-sec/mi-laboratorio-log4shell","description":"Laboratorio automatizado Plug & Play en Docker para auditar y estudiar la vulnerabilidad Log4Shell (CVE-2021-44228)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Apache Log4j2 2.0-beta9 through 2.15.0 (excluding security releases 2.12.2, 2.12.3, and 2.3.1) JNDI features used in configuration, log messages, and parameters do not protect against attacker controlled LDAP and other JNDI related endpoints. An attacker who can control log messages or log message parameters can execute arbitrary code loaded from LDAP servers when message lookup substitution is enabled. From log4j 2.15.0, this behavior has been disabled by default. From version 2.16.0 (along with 2.12.2, 2.12.3, and 2.3.1), this functionality has been completely removed. Note that this vulnerability is specific to log4j-core and does not affect log4net, log4cxx, or other Apache Logging Services projects.","created_at":"2026-05-18 09:59:16","updated_at":"2026-05-18 10:23:03","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 10:23:00","inserted_at":"2026-05-18 16:36:31","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1241915219","cve_id":"CVE-2026-36438","name":"CVE-2026-36438","owner":"kensh1k","full_name":"kensh1k/CVE-2026-36438","html_url":"https://github.com/kensh1k/CVE-2026-36438","description":"This repository contains information about the CVE-2026-36438","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"An issue in Intelbras VIP-1230-D-G4 Version V2.800.00IB00C.0.T allows a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information via password reset functionality under /OutsideCmd","created_at":"2026-05-18 09:53:43","updated_at":"2026-05-18 10:17:40","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 10:17:37","inserted_at":"2026-05-18 16:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1241902854","cve_id":"CVE-2024-37054","name":"CVE-2024-37054-PoC","owner":"jimmexploit","full_name":"jimmexploit/CVE-2024-37054-PoC","html_url":"https://github.com/jimmexploit/CVE-2024-37054-PoC","description":"PoC for CVE-2024-37054","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Deserialization of untrusted data can occur in versions of the MLflow platform running version 0.9.0 or newer, enabling a maliciously uploaded PyFunc model to run arbitrary code on an end user’s system when interacted with.","created_at":"2026-05-18 09:27:12","updated_at":"2026-05-18 09:35:04","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 09:35:01","inserted_at":"2026-05-18 10:36:32","cvss_score":8.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1241834592","cve_id":"CVE-2026-8181","name":"CVE-2026-8181","owner":"xShadow-Here","full_name":"xShadow-Here/CVE-2026-8181","html_url":"https://github.com/xShadow-Here/CVE-2026-8181","description":"CVE-2026-8181 | Burst Statistics 3.4.0 - 3.4.1.1 - Authentication Bypass to Admin Account Takeover ","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"The Burst Statistics – Privacy-Friendly WordPress Analytics (Google Analytics Alternative) plugin for WordPress is vulnerable to Authentication Bypass in versions 3.4.0 to 3.4.1.1. This is due to incorrect return-value handling in the `is_mainwp_authenticated()` function when validating application passwords from the Authorization header. This makes it possible for unauthenticated attackers, with knowledge of an administrator username, to impersonate that administrator for the duration of the request by supplying any random Basic Authentication password achieving privilege escalation.","created_at":"2026-05-18 06:47:54","updated_at":"2026-05-18 06:51:11","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 06:51:07","inserted_at":"2026-05-18 10:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1241819733","cve_id":"CVE-2026-3629","name":"CVE-2026-3629","owner":"PySecTools","full_name":"PySecTools/CVE-2026-3629","html_url":"https://github.com/PySecTools/CVE-2026-3629","description":"WordPress Privilege Escalation Checker","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"The Import and export users and customers plugin for WordPress is vulnerable to privilege escalation in all versions up to, and including, 1.29.7. This is due to the 'save_extra_user_profile_fields' function not properly restricting which user meta keys can be updated via profile fields. The 'get_restricted_fields' method does not include sensitive meta keys such as 'wp_capabilities'. This makes it possible for unauthenticated attackers to escalate their privileges to Administrator by submitting a crafted registration request that sets the 'wp_capabilities' meta key. The vulnerability can only be exploited if the \"Show fields in profile\" setting is enabled and a CSV with a wp_capabilities column header has been previously imported.","created_at":"2026-05-18 06:18:10","updated_at":"2026-05-18 06:51:34","pushed_at":"2026-05-18 06:51:30","inserted_at":"2026-05-18 10:36:33","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"}]}]}],["$Lb"],"$Lc"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"UmQ1hoF6yzsRD_eMmg_pb"}
b:["$","script","script-0",{"src":"/_next/static/chunks/0m~z_00mur5o..js","async":true}]
